The basic premise of this routine goes back decades. Magicians often 
perform classic pieces but the challenge is to "make it their own" by

comments.text:
It's not Carl Einar's either. Justin Willman actually made the routine more 
of his own than Carl did by including the (failing) banana suit prediction 
in the beginning and above all by incorporating Siri. Mr Einar performed 
just the classic version exactly as put together by Tom Yarbrough, dating 
back to 1969. Anyhow, a whole lot of magicians have performed this trick, 
David Copperfield included so no need to be upset at Mr Willman for doing 
it as well.
